<span id="freeTextContainer17480456448068162986">When Jesus said that bit about &quot;suffer the little children&quot; this may not have been what he had in mind...<br/><br/>(Yeah, yeah, &quot;suffer&quot; in ye olden times meant &quot;allow&quot; or &quot;tolerate&quot; - just let me have the dang joke, OK?)<br/><br/><i>Mother said, “And here’s the Herdman family. We’re glad to see you all,” which was probably the biggest lie ever said right out loud in the church.</i> (38)<br/><br/>Our straight-shootin&apos; no-nonsense but nameless narrator tells it like it is, as only an eight-year-old can. Out of the mouths of babes, a</span>
  <span id="freeText17480456448068162986" style="display:none">When Jesus said that bit about "suffer the little children" this may not have been what he had in mind...<br /><br />(Yeah, yeah, "suffer" in ye olden times meant "allow" or "tolerate" - just let me have the dang joke, OK?)<br /><br /><i>Mother said, “And here’s the Herdman family. We’re glad to see you all,” which was probably the biggest lie ever said right out loud in the church.</i> (38)<br /><br />Our straight-shootin' no-nonsense but nameless narrator tells it like it is, as only an eight-year-old can. Out of the mouths of babes, and all that. (Whoa, a Bible quote twofer? 'Tis the season!)<br /><br />4 stars - rollicking good fun, which by the way Wikipedia claims is "a modern day retelling of the medieval Second Shepherds' Play," and don't that just beat all.</span>
