<span id="freeTextContainer8297956334406547977">An unruly pack of siblings, the Herdmans terrorize the school, back in the day when bullying, neglected children, and vandalism were hilarious. The girls smoke cigars in the bathroom!—what could be funnier than that?<br/><br/>This seasonal classic was unknown to me. The illustrations in this edition are grim and murky, like something out of Dickens. It does manage to be amusing, in that it is appropriately over the top and makes fun of everybody, even the minister&apos;s wife and the local busybody. The pagean</span>
  <span id="freeText8297956334406547977" style="display:none">An unruly pack of siblings, the Herdmans terrorize the school, back in the day when bullying, neglected children, and vandalism were hilarious. The girls smoke cigars in the bathroom!—what could be funnier than that?<br /><br />This seasonal classic was unknown to me. The illustrations in this edition are grim and murky, like something out of Dickens. It does manage to be amusing, in that it is appropriately over the top and makes fun of everybody, even the minister's wife and the local busybody. The pageant promises to be a spectacular disaster, but somehow, even in a children's book aimed at the Christmas market, contrives to provide some guidance on the true meaning of the season. What a plot twist!<br /><br />There. Now my seasonal activities are all taken care of. Time to hibernate until a chorus of songbirds wake me in the spring.</span>
