  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_4168869399" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4168869399" />
    <a title="Jenna Marie ~Let it Snow~" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/134893951-jenna-marie-let-it-snow"><img alt="Jenna Marie ~Let it Snow~" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1632835833p2/134893951.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4168869399?book_show_action=true">Aug 11, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jenna Marie ~Let it Snow~" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jenna Marie ~Let it Snow~" href="/user/show/134893951-jenna-marie-let-it-snow">Jenna Marie ~Let it Snow~</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audio CD 9780061215223" href="/book/show/420342.The_Best_Christmas_Pageant_Ever">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4168869399" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9548454369270939382">In their small town, the Christmas Pageant is the exact same every year, down to every boring detail. It almost seems useless to cast the characters, for the cast remains the same every year. Until, that is, the Herdmans&apos; children decide they want to attend.<br/><br/>The Herdmans children are known for being rambunctious and disobedient, prancing across town and always getting their way in the most tremendous crimes. When they decide they want to join the yearly Christmas Pageant, everyone knows this page</span>
  <span id="freeText9548454369270939382" style="display:none">In their small town, the Christmas Pageant is the exact same every year, down to every boring detail. It almost seems useless to cast the characters, for the cast remains the same every year. Until, that is, the Herdmans' children decide they want to attend.<br /><br />The Herdmans children are known for being rambunctious and disobedient, prancing across town and always getting their way in the most tremendous crimes. When they decide they want to join the yearly Christmas Pageant, everyone knows this pageant is going to be far from normal. <br /><br />Sure enough, everything seems to go wrong as the practices begin. Everyone is sure, the Herdmans are going to destroy their play! Still, there seems to be nothing they can do. When the opening night comes, everyone is ready for a disaster. Until the play begins, and the Herdmans put on a show like none other. <br /><br />This book is short and simple, yet adorable, with a wonderful moral and ending. It is a great Christmas read for children of all ages that even adults can enjoy, and it would be a perfect family read over the holidays! I enjoyed it, and while it was a rather simple book, I would recommend.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9548454369270939382" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

